main event: A flying object was observed over Gurnee, Illinois on August 11, 1955.
interesting points: The object exhibited both linear and elliptical shapes.
More than one object was reported by the witness.
Lights were observed on the objects.
The objects appeared to be traveling at varying speeds and on varying courses across the horizon.
The witness was considered to be reliable, and the object could not be identified as any known type of aircraft.
sighted object: one or more unidentified flying objects
photographs: no photographs present in the report
